This isn't a game,
man.

262
00:11:00,460 --> 00:11:01,560
I'm serious.
Okay.

263
00:11:01,594 --> 00:11:04,204
Put your damn phone and wallet
on the ground right now.

264
00:11:04,231 --> 00:11:06,271
Hey, do you see this, man?
I am not playing around!

265
00:11:06,299 --> 00:11:08,739
Just put your phone and wallet
on the damn ground!

266
00:11:08,769 --> 00:11:10,239
Come on, man, just --
just do what he says!

267
00:11:10,270 --> 00:11:11,240
Please listen to him.

268
00:11:11,271 --> 00:11:13,411
Shut up! Just shut up
and get on your knees!

269
00:11:13,440 --> 00:11:15,310
Put your hands and knees
on the ground.

270
00:11:15,342 --> 00:11:17,082
Get your wallet out
right now. Hey!

271
00:11:17,110 --> 00:11:19,280
I will shoot your crazy ass,
I swear to God.
Okay.

272
00:11:19,312 --> 00:11:21,052
Are you listening to me?!
I'll do it!
Yes.

273
00:11:21,081 --> 00:11:22,821
Hey!
You hear me?

274
00:11:22,850 --> 00:11:24,180
Hey!
[ Gunshot ]

275
00:11:24,217 --> 00:11:26,947
[ Breathing heavily ]

276
00:11:26,987 --> 00:11:30,757
**

277
00:11:31,859 --> 00:11:33,059
[ Whimpering ]

278
00:11:33,093 --> 00:11:34,193
Oh, my God!

279
00:11:34,227 --> 00:11:37,827
**

280
00:11:37,865 --> 00:11:39,825
[ Avery crying ]

281
00:11:39,867 --> 00:11:44,237
**

282
00:11:45,272 --> 00:11:47,042
Okay.

283
00:11:47,074 --> 00:11:49,044
You need to take
the rest of the day off.

284
00:11:49,076 --> 00:11:50,936
Dr. Melendez
said that, too.

285
00:11:50,978 --> 00:11:51,948
Why?
"Why?"

286
00:11:51,979 --> 00:11:54,479
Because you just experienced
a traumatic event.

287
00:11:54,514 --> 00:11:56,724
It's not my fault.
I-I know that.

288
00:11:57,550 --> 00:11:59,450
Avery has
multiple injuries.

289
00:11:59,486 --> 00:12:02,416
Dr. Melendez wants me
to monitor her.

290
00:12:05,893 --> 00:12:07,863
[ Door beeps ]

291
00:12:07,895 --> 00:12:09,425
[ Chatter ]

292
00:12:09,462 --> 00:12:11,002
Dr. Lim.

293
00:12:13,100 --> 00:12:13,900
I was out of line.

294
00:12:13,934 --> 00:12:15,304
I shouldn't have argued
with you.

295
00:12:15,335 --> 00:12:16,765
Primary enclosure
went well.

296
00:12:16,804 --> 00:12:18,344
We'll extubate him
in a few hours

297
00:12:18,371 --> 00:12:20,411
to prevent any further
internal damage.

298
00:12:20,440 --> 00:12:21,510
Well,
that's good.

299
00:12:21,541 --> 00:12:23,811
It is, and you're gonna
make sure he stays that way.

300
00:12:23,844 --> 00:12:27,414
You'll be babysitting
tonight in the ICU.

301
00:12:27,447 --> 00:12:29,947
I'm --
I'm not on call.

302
00:12:29,983 --> 00:12:30,953
Great,
then you're available.

303
00:12:30,984 --> 00:12:32,124
Should be
a quiet night.

304
00:12:32,152 --> 00:12:33,992
Just want to keep an eye
on those vitals.

305
00:12:34,021 --> 00:12:35,491
You never know
with tracheal tears.

306
00:12:35,522 --> 00:12:36,292
[ Chuckles ]

307
00:12:36,323 --> 00:12:38,193
Can't one of
the ICU nurses do that?

308
00:12:38,225 --> 00:12:39,225
Yep.

309
00:12:39,259 --> 00:12:41,359
But they didn't lip off
in my operating room.

310
00:12:41,394 --> 00:12:43,964
And he'd better be breathing
in the morning.

311
00:12:43,997 --> 00:12:46,367
**

312
00:12:49,102 --> 00:12:53,042
Excuse me, but why is Shaun
on the victim's case?

313
00:12:53,073 --> 00:12:55,013
I assessed him,
and he seemed perfectly capable.

314
00:12:55,042 --> 00:12:56,112
You assessed him?

315
00:12:56,143 --> 00:12:58,213
What does that mean? You asked
him how he was feeling?

316
00:12:58,245 --> 00:12:59,205
You psychic?

317
00:12:59,246 --> 00:13:02,246
D-Do you have an advanced degree
in psychology?

318
00:13:02,282 --> 00:13:04,452
You don't know
what's going on in his head.

319
00:13:06,887 --> 00:13:09,117
When I'm in surgery,
my focus is on the person

320
00:13:09,156 --> 00:13:10,386
whose guts are open
in front of me

321
00:13:10,423 --> 00:13:12,593
rather than the soul of the
person standing across from me.

322
00:13:12,625 --> 00:13:16,155
No.
And it seems that Shaun doesn't
let anything impact his work.

323
00:13:16,196 --> 00:13:17,866
So, along with
his photographic memory,

324
00:13:17,898 --> 00:13:20,068
I'm putting cold-hearted
in the plus column.

325
00:13:20,100 --> 00:13:23,100
**

326
00:13:26,173 --> 00:13:30,013
Dr. Murphy, do you understand
why you're here?

327
00:13:30,043 --> 00:13:30,913
Yes.

328
00:13:30,944 --> 00:13:34,014
Dr. Glassman said
I had to talk to you.

329
00:13:34,047 --> 00:13:36,877
After any doctor goes through
a potentially traumatic --

330
00:13:36,917 --> 00:13:39,287
You have to determine
if I'm a medicolegal liability

331
00:13:39,319 --> 00:13:41,289
to the hospital.
Yes.

332
00:13:41,321 --> 00:13:43,891
And, more importantly,
it's an opportunity

333
00:13:43,924 --> 00:13:46,234
to provide you
with emotional support.

334
00:13:50,263 --> 00:13:52,433
How are you feeling?

335
00:13:53,600 --> 00:13:55,970
You don't have apples.

336
00:13:57,404 --> 00:14:00,374
I'll try to have some fruit
next time we meet.

337
00:14:00,407 --> 00:14:02,507
Good.

338
00:14:03,911 --> 00:14:07,111
Do you regret anything
about this morning?

339
00:14:08,215 --> 00:14:10,475
Why?

340
00:14:10,517 --> 00:14:12,047
After bad things happen,

341
00:14:12,085 --> 00:14:14,045
it's perfectly normal
to replay the events,

342
00:14:14,087 --> 00:14:15,887
wishing you had
done things differently.

343
00:14:15,923 --> 00:14:17,463
It already happened.

344
00:14:17,490 --> 00:14:20,260
I can't
do things differently.

345
00:14:21,361 --> 00:14:23,861
Is talking about this
upsetting you?

346
00:14:28,301 --> 00:14:30,541
What are you
thinking about right now?

347
00:14:32,172 --> 00:14:36,442
Systemic Inflammatory
Response Syndrome.

348
00:14:38,378 --> 00:14:40,278
Melendez:
The surgery went well.

349
00:14:40,313 --> 00:14:42,283
After a serious trauma
like this,

350
00:14:42,315 --> 00:14:43,445
the body can develop

351
00:14:43,483 --> 00:14:45,953
a self-destructive
inflammatory reaction.

352
00:14:45,986 --> 00:14:48,016
Kidneys, liver,
lungs, heart --

353
00:14:48,055 --> 00:14:50,555
any or all of them
can start to shut down.

354
00:14:50,590 --> 00:14:52,660
We'll be giving her
anti-inflammatories

355
00:14:52,692 --> 00:14:54,192
and monitoring her closely,

356
00:14:54,227 --> 00:14:56,557
but the next 24 hours
are critical.
Okay.

357
00:14:56,596 --> 00:14:57,596
Thanks.

358
00:14:57,630 --> 00:14:59,330
Just get her through this.
Whatever you got to do.

359
00:14:59,366 --> 00:15:01,096
Yeah, well,
I need consent forms

360
00:15:01,134 --> 00:15:02,504
from your girlfriend's
next of kin.

361
00:15:02,535 --> 00:15:05,065
If you could please
get her family in here

362
00:15:05,105 --> 00:15:06,565
as quickly
as possible.

363
00:15:09,676 --> 00:15:13,576
I can't. I...

364
00:15:13,613 --> 00:15:15,183
**

365
00:15:15,215 --> 00:15:17,675
I don't even know
her last name.

366
00:15:17,717 --> 00:15:19,247
It was
our first date.

367
00:15:19,286 --> 00:15:20,646
W-We met
on a dating app.

368
00:15:20,687 --> 00:15:21,957
We were going hiking,

369
00:15:21,989 --> 00:15:23,989
so she wasn't carrying
a purse or ID.

370
00:15:24,024 --> 00:15:27,464
Well, then, you really
don't need to be here.

371
00:15:27,494 --> 00:15:29,464
**

372
00:15:29,496 --> 00:15:32,066
Someone out there
cares about her.

373
00:15:32,099 --> 00:15:32,999
If she dies,

374
00:15:33,033 --> 00:15:35,343
I want them to know
someone was with her.

375
00:15:35,368 --> 00:15:38,268
**

376
00:15:38,305 --> 00:15:41,665
I'll have social work
try to locate her family.

377
00:15:41,708 --> 00:15:42,678
**

378
00:15:42,709 --> 00:15:44,739
Stay as long
as you want.

379
00:15:44,777 --> 00:15:50,947
**

380
00:15:55,388 --> 00:15:58,388
It looks clean,
dry, and healthy.

381
00:15:58,425 --> 00:15:59,655
My neck
is killing me.

382
00:16:02,729 --> 00:16:04,299
How long
have you been using?

383
00:16:04,331 --> 00:16:06,331
What's that got to do
with anything?

384
00:16:06,366 --> 00:16:09,166
Well, you likely built up
a tolerance to pain meds.

385
00:16:09,202 --> 00:16:11,102
Now that you really need them,
they aren't there for you.

386
00:16:11,138 --> 00:16:12,438
That's why
I need fentanyl.

387
00:16:12,472 --> 00:16:14,542
100 micrograms.
Are you gonna help me or not?

388
00:16:14,574 --> 00:16:15,644
That wouldn't be helping.

389
00:16:15,675 --> 00:16:17,505
The worst thing I can do for you
is feed your habit.

390
00:16:17,544 --> 00:16:18,784
[ Scoffs ]

391
00:16:18,811 --> 00:16:20,381
[ Chuckles ]

392
00:16:20,413 --> 00:16:21,553
What?

393
00:16:21,581 --> 00:16:24,351
You saw my tattoo.

394
00:16:24,384 --> 00:16:25,524
Yeah.

395
00:16:25,552 --> 00:16:27,022
And now
you're punishing me.

396
00:16:27,054 --> 00:16:28,524
You wa this
to hurt.

397
00:16:28,555 --> 00:16:30,385
I'm treating you professionally.
If you were
treating me professionally,

398
00:16:30,423 --> 00:16:32,293
I wouldn't be
in so much pain.
I'm sorry,
but I --

399
00:16:32,325 --> 00:16:34,385
Just give me
the damn drugs!

400
00:16:34,427 --> 00:16:36,427
Come on!

401
00:16:36,463 --> 00:16:45,273
**

402
00:16:51,111 --> 00:16:55,351
Melendez thinks that he's okay
being on Avery's case.

403
00:16:55,382 --> 00:16:56,482
I don't.

404
00:16:56,516 --> 00:16:58,616
Dr. Melendez
may be right.

405
00:16:58,651 --> 00:17:01,121
That case seems to be
Shaun's primary focus right now.

406
00:17:01,154 --> 00:17:03,764
Maybe his condition is
a blessing in this situation.

407
00:17:03,790 --> 00:17:05,160
Maybe?

408
00:17:05,192 --> 00:17:06,432
Or obsessing
over Avery's health

409
00:17:06,459 --> 00:17:08,329
could be his only outlet
for a guilty conscience.

410
00:17:08,361 --> 00:17:10,701
Watching her suffer could just
be worsening those feelings.

411
00:17:10,730 --> 00:17:12,200
So, either it's
a huge problem

412
00:17:12,232 --> 00:17:13,502
or it's not a problem
at all.

413
00:17:13,533 --> 00:17:15,773
This is
your professional opinion?

414
00:17:15,802 --> 00:17:17,602
Shaun has
a very unique mind

415
00:17:17,637 --> 00:17:19,837
and an incredibly
introverted nature.

416
00:17:19,872 --> 00:17:22,442
**

417
00:17:22,475 --> 00:17:25,105
Well,
thank you for that.

418
00:17:25,145 --> 00:17:28,515
I'm sorry, but without
a lot more time with him,

419
00:17:28,548 --> 00:17:29,778
that's the best
I can offer.

420
00:17:29,816 --> 00:17:36,716
**

421
00:17:38,158 --> 00:17:39,758
What did Lim
expect me to do --

422
00:17:39,792 --> 00:17:40,862
stand there
and smile

423
00:17:40,893 --> 00:17:43,533
while she called my
medical judgment into question?

424
00:17:43,563 --> 00:17:46,103
Your patient nearly died
waiting on that O.R., right?

425
00:17:46,133 --> 00:17:47,803
It was bad.
What do you want me to do?

426
00:17:47,834 --> 00:17:49,104
Tell her
to back off!

427
00:17:49,136 --> 00:17:50,666
No.
He's a complete
and utter --

428
00:17:50,703 --> 00:17:52,413
Not one of those
nice racists, huh?

429
00:17:52,439 --> 00:17:54,269
I shouldn't
have to be --
Claire!

430
00:17:54,307 --> 00:17:55,407
Here's what
you have to do --

431
00:17:55,442 --> 00:17:58,152
shut up and do exactly
what Dr. Lim tells you to do.

432
00:17:58,178 --> 00:17:59,608
But --

433
00:17:59,646 --> 00:18:01,206
**

434
00:18:01,248 --> 00:18:04,778
Yes, sir.

435
00:18:04,817 --> 00:18:08,487
**

436
00:18:12,459 --> 00:18:14,559
Maybe we could
take turns.

437
00:18:14,594 --> 00:18:16,704
You can keep an eye
on my patient,

438
00:18:16,729 --> 00:18:18,299
I keep an eye
on yours.

439
00:18:18,331 --> 00:18:19,371
No.

440
00:18:19,399 --> 00:18:21,269
[ Sighs ]

441
00:18:21,301 --> 00:18:25,441
Her creatinine
is 1.6.

442
00:18:25,472 --> 00:18:27,172
Mild bump
in renal numbers

443
00:18:27,207 --> 00:18:29,507
isn't surprising
after all her trauma.

444
00:18:34,481 --> 00:18:37,181
This morning
must've been crazy.

445
00:18:37,217 --> 00:18:38,647
Are you okay?

446
00:18:40,353 --> 00:18:41,293
This morning,

447
00:18:41,321 --> 00:18:43,761
my neighbor Lea came over
and ate my apple.

448
00:18:43,790 --> 00:18:46,530
That's too bad.

449
00:18:46,559 --> 00:18:48,299
Yes,
it was my last one.

450
00:18:48,328 --> 00:18:50,798
She was upset with Armen,
our landlord.

451
00:18:50,830 --> 00:18:52,930
She plays her music
very loud.

452
00:18:52,965 --> 00:18:54,725
I gave her some advice.

453
00:18:54,767 --> 00:18:55,867
It seemed
to anger her

454
00:18:55,902 --> 00:18:59,212
because she left
without saying goodbye.

455
00:18:59,239 --> 00:19:02,209
And you think
you did something wrong.

456
00:19:02,242 --> 00:19:04,542
No,
it was good advice.

457
00:19:04,577 --> 00:19:07,877
Shaun, sometimes a woman
wants advice,

458
00:19:07,914 --> 00:19:10,454
and sometimes
she just wants support.

459
00:19:11,851 --> 00:19:15,521
How can I tell
which one Lea wants?

460
00:19:15,555 --> 00:19:16,515
**

461
00:19:16,556 --> 00:19:18,456
Err on
the side of support.

462
00:19:18,491 --> 00:19:20,331
That's not helpful.
Yes, it is.

463
00:19:20,360 --> 00:19:22,630
Dr. Browne.
You're being summoned.

464
00:19:22,662 --> 00:19:25,902
[ Inhales deeply,
sighs ]

465
00:19:25,932 --> 00:19:28,702
All right.

466
00:19:28,735 --> 00:19:30,695
**

467
00:19:30,737 --> 00:19:33,737
About time.

468
00:19:35,308 --> 00:19:37,438
All your struggling,
you've pulled out your IV.

469
00:19:38,878 --> 00:19:42,318
Aren't nurses usually supposed
to do this kind of crap?

470
00:19:43,950 --> 00:19:46,390
They let you
go to med school,

471
00:19:46,419 --> 00:19:48,759
but they don't trust you
with any real responsibility.

472
00:19:48,788 --> 00:19:52,258
There must be a competent doctor
tucked around here somewhere

473
00:19:52,292 --> 00:19:54,462
who tell someone
I need more than aspirin.

474
00:19:54,494 --> 00:19:56,504
"Competent"?
Yeah.

475
00:19:56,529 --> 00:19:58,369
You know
what I mean.

476
00:19:59,766 --> 00:20:02,936
Imhotep was the father
of modern medicine.

477
00:20:02,969 --> 00:20:04,699
An Egyptian.
Yeah.

478
00:20:04,737 --> 00:20:06,467
Good for your people.

479
00:20:06,506 --> 00:20:07,536
[ Scoffs ]

480
00:20:07,574 --> 00:20:09,814
I'm willing to bet there's even
been a couple others

481
00:20:09,842 --> 00:20:12,682
over the last 3,000 years,
but guess what?

482
00:20:12,712 --> 00:20:13,712
On average,

483
00:20:13,746 --> 00:20:16,416
you look at most great
technological advancements,

484
00:20:16,449 --> 00:20:18,449
you'll find
a proud Northern European

485
00:20:18,485 --> 00:20:19,485
holding the patent.

486
00:20:19,519 --> 00:20:20,549
[ Scoffs ]

487
00:20:20,587 --> 00:20:22,357
That's what you were trying
to do this morning?

488
00:20:22,389 --> 00:20:23,959
Get the patent
on stealing 30 bucks

489
00:20:23,990 --> 00:20:26,730
from the corner store
for a drug fix?

490
00:20:26,759 --> 00:20:29,259
You don't like drug addicts,
do you?

491
00:20:30,297 --> 00:20:32,997
Mm, a lot of people
I don't like.

492
00:20:33,032 --> 00:20:38,712
Thieves, racists,
violent punks,

493
00:20:38,738 --> 00:20:40,768
but I'll treat 'em.

494
00:20:42,742 --> 00:20:44,842
Was your mama
a drug addict?

495
00:20:44,877 --> 00:20:46,877
Wow.

496
00:20:46,913 --> 00:20:49,453
That's the beauty
of cliches,

497
00:20:49,482 --> 00:20:51,352
is they're true
so often, huh?

498
00:20:51,384 --> 00:20:53,824
You don't know anything
about me.

499
00:20:53,853 --> 00:20:55,793
I didn't go
to college.

500
00:20:55,822 --> 00:20:58,632
I didn't have no
affirmative action to get me in,

501
00:20:58,658 --> 00:20:59,828
but you did.

502
00:20:59,859 --> 00:21:02,829
All because some bleeding-heart
liberal in the Dean's office

503
00:21:02,862 --> 00:21:05,772
teared up reading your essay
about your crack-whore mama.

504
00:21:05,798 --> 00:21:08,298
Aah!
What the hell?

505
00:21:08,335 --> 00:21:10,965
[ Groans, chuckles ]

506
00:21:12,539 --> 00:21:14,309
I guess
we're all violent punks.

507
00:21:17,577 --> 00:21:20,577
[ Monitors beeping ]

508
00:21:30,823 --> 00:21:34,363
All you had to do
was give him your wallet.

509
00:21:41,501 --> 00:21:44,701
**

510
00:21:48,107 --> 00:21:51,937
Her urine output
is low.

511
00:21:51,978 --> 00:21:53,748
Whoa, whoa,
what are you doing?!

512
00:21:53,780 --> 00:21:55,080
Get away from her!
Hey!

513
00:21:55,114 --> 00:21:57,054
You can't be in here
shoving my doctors around.

514
00:21:57,083 --> 00:21:59,723
Me?
He -- He's the --

515
00:21:59,752 --> 00:22:01,122
**

516
00:22:01,153 --> 00:22:03,393
Oh, my God.
She needs dialysis.

517
00:22:03,423 --> 00:22:04,863
Her kidneys
are failing fast.

518
00:22:04,891 --> 00:22:09,401
This is the first stage
of total organ failure.

519
00:22:09,429 --> 00:22:11,059
**

520
00:22:15,001 --> 00:22:16,141
[ Monitors beeping ]

521
00:22:16,168 --> 00:22:19,108
Shaun: We removed two liters
of excess fluid with dialysis,

522
00:22:19,138 --> 00:22:20,538
but she's getting worse.

523
00:22:20,573 --> 00:22:22,443
Fluid's building up
in her chest.

524
00:22:22,475 --> 00:22:23,905
She's in
pulmonary failure, too.

525
00:22:23,943 --> 00:22:25,813
Draining the fluid
in her pleural space

526
00:22:25,845 --> 00:22:27,545
would reduce
airway resistance.

527
00:22:27,580 --> 00:22:29,880
Yeah, let's prep her
for a thoracentesis.

528
00:22:29,916 --> 00:22:31,616
We're gonna have to
work fast.

529
00:22:31,651 --> 00:22:33,091
I'll prep
the evac drain.

530
00:22:33,119 --> 00:22:35,619
I'm gonna need you to put
that needle right between --

531
00:22:35,655 --> 00:22:36,815
6th and 7th rib.

532
00:22:36,856 --> 00:22:38,626
[ Monitors beeping rapidly ]

533
00:22:38,658 --> 00:22:45,098
**

534
00:22:45,131 --> 00:22:46,701
Wait, you're gonna
let h do --

535
00:22:46,733 --> 00:22:48,103
Shut up.
All right, careful.

536
00:22:48,134 --> 00:22:49,674
Don't put the needle in
too deep.

537
00:22:49,702 --> 00:22:51,602
We don't want
to give her --
Pneumothorax.

538
00:22:51,638 --> 00:22:53,138
[ Monitors beeping rapidly ]

539
00:22:53,172 --> 00:22:54,642
All right,
you're in.

540
00:22:54,674 --> 00:22:56,844
**

541
00:22:56,876 --> 00:22:59,906
Now, let me see
what I can pull out.

542
00:22:59,946 --> 00:23:01,476
[ Beeping continues ]

543
00:23:01,514 --> 00:23:03,654
Hopefully
she settles down.

544
00:23:03,683 --> 00:23:06,193
[ Beeping continues ]

545
00:23:06,218 --> 00:23:14,658
**

546
00:23:19,932 --> 00:23:21,072
CO2's down,
and O2's climbing.

547
00:23:21,100 --> 00:23:22,400
[ Monitors beeping ]

548
00:23:24,070 --> 00:23:25,000
We can manage her kidneys
and her lungs,

549
00:23:25,037 --> 00:23:26,737
but the last stop
in multiple organ failure

550
00:23:26,773 --> 00:23:27,673
would be her heart.

551
00:23:27,707 --> 00:23:30,737
Watch her ventilation pressures
like a hawk,

552
00:23:30,777 --> 00:23:34,807
push cardioprotective meds,
and page me if anything changes.

553
00:23:36,983 --> 00:23:38,923
Think you're being
her hero?

554
00:23:38,951 --> 00:23:41,021
The fact is
you hardly know her.

555
00:23:41,053 --> 00:23:43,493
And you don't
know him at all.

556
00:23:43,523 --> 00:23:45,093
Go home.

557
00:23:45,124 --> 00:23:49,834
[ Monitors beeping ]

558
00:23:51,197 --> 00:23:52,967
[ Knock on door ]
Yep.

559
00:23:59,806 --> 00:24:01,106
Okay,
I am done.

560
00:24:01,140 --> 00:24:03,510
He's a foul-mouthed,
spiteful bully.

561
00:24:03,543 --> 00:24:04,643
No problem.

562
00:24:04,677 --> 00:24:06,507
I'll have the concierge
find a patient

563
00:24:06,546 --> 00:24:08,146
more suited
to your liking.

564
00:24:08,180 --> 00:24:10,780
He doesn't need a doctor
doting over him.

565
00:24:10,817 --> 00:24:12,247
He doesn't want me.

566
00:24:12,284 --> 00:24:13,594
I don't care.

567
00:24:13,620 --> 00:24:17,060
I'm sorry I disagreed
with you, okay?

568
00:24:17,089 --> 00:24:20,659
But I don't deserve
to be scolded like a school girl

569
00:24:20,693 --> 00:24:23,633
because your ego can't handle
being challenged a little.

570
00:24:23,663 --> 00:24:24,733
[ Chuckling ] Oh.

571
00:24:24,764 --> 00:24:26,204
That is
some apology.

572
00:24:26,232 --> 00:24:27,802
Look,
I had a legitimate --

573
00:24:27,834 --> 00:24:29,204
You really
don't see the problem here?

574
00:24:29,235 --> 00:24:31,565
What? [ Chuckles ]
With challenging you?

575
00:24:32,605 --> 00:24:35,635
Right now,
you are confronting me

576
00:24:35,675 --> 00:24:37,635
in front
of two nurses.

577
00:24:37,677 --> 00:24:39,707
Would you do that
to Melendez?

578
00:24:39,746 --> 00:24:41,806
Or would you wait
five minutes?

579
00:24:41,848 --> 00:24:44,548
**

580
00:24:44,584 --> 00:24:45,754
I have dealt with men

581
00:24:45,785 --> 00:24:48,115
undermining my authority
my entire career.

582
00:24:48,154 --> 00:24:50,564
We shouldn't do it
to one another, too.

583
00:24:50,590 --> 00:24:54,090
Now go take care of him like
you would any other patient.

584
00:24:54,126 --> 00:24:59,826
[ Equipment whirring ]

585
00:24:59,866 --> 00:25:01,926
**

586
00:25:01,968 --> 00:25:03,538
**

587
00:25:03,570 --> 00:25:05,710
Hey.
Hey! Hey!

588
00:25:05,738 --> 00:25:08,578
Food services --
they double-check every order.

589
00:25:08,608 --> 00:25:09,638
What are you looking for?

590
00:25:09,676 --> 00:25:10,676
An apple.
An apple?

591
00:25:10,710 --> 00:25:12,040
Who's getting an apple?
I am!

592
00:25:12,078 --> 00:25:13,178
No.
Glassman: Shaun.

593
00:25:13,212 --> 00:25:15,152
Forget the apple,
please.

594
00:25:15,181 --> 00:25:16,851
I'm sorry.
Can I have a minute?

595
00:25:16,883 --> 00:25:18,083
Shaun?

596
00:25:19,686 --> 00:25:21,916
Okay.

597
00:25:23,590 --> 00:25:25,260
[ Clears throat ]

598
00:25:25,291 --> 00:25:27,861
Shaun, there's no need
to get defensive, okay?

599
00:25:27,894 --> 00:25:29,034
Do you want
to sit down?

600
00:25:29,061 --> 00:25:31,261
No, thank you.

601
00:25:31,297 --> 00:25:34,127
I want you
to tell me again

602
00:25:34,166 --> 00:25:35,836
exactly what happened
this morning.

603
00:25:35,868 --> 00:25:37,868
I told you exactly
what happened this morning.

604
00:25:37,904 --> 00:25:40,714
Yes, but people have told you
that it's your fault.

605
00:25:40,740 --> 00:25:41,910
Haven't they?

606
00:25:41,941 --> 00:25:45,211
My actions and the shooting
were associative incidents.

607
00:25:45,244 --> 00:25:47,654
It is not
a causal relationship.

608
00:25:47,680 --> 00:25:48,780
I paced,
and she got shot,

609
00:25:48,815 --> 00:25:50,145
but pacing
doesn't cause shootings,

610
00:25:50,182 --> 00:25:51,722
otherwise every time
someone paced,

611
00:25:51,751 --> 00:25:52,951
a shooting
would soon follow.

612
00:25:52,985 --> 00:25:55,085
Okay,
that's a very good point.

613
00:25:57,724 --> 00:25:59,894
When someone has
a gun

614
00:25:59,926 --> 00:26:03,156
and it's
a dangerous situation, right?

615
00:26:03,195 --> 00:26:06,025
You don't want
to upset the situation.

616
00:26:06,065 --> 00:26:07,695
You don't want
to make it worse.

617
00:26:07,734 --> 00:26:10,644
You think
this is my fault, too.

618
00:26:10,670 --> 00:26:13,040
No, no,
it was the shoot--

619
00:26:13,072 --> 00:26:14,312
[ Chuckles, sighs ]

620
00:26:14,340 --> 00:26:16,040
It was
the shooter's fault,

621
00:26:16,075 --> 00:26:19,045
but your actions
may have contributed to it.

622
00:26:19,078 --> 00:26:20,778
Okay, Shaun,
wait a second.

623
00:26:20,813 --> 00:26:21,983
Wait a second.

624
00:26:22,014 --> 00:26:25,324
I know your behavior is not
completely in your control,

625
00:26:25,351 --> 00:26:27,691
but I also know it's not
completely out of your control.

626
00:26:27,720 --> 00:26:28,620
Is it?

627
00:26:28,655 --> 00:26:34,055
So, yes, maybe it is
a little bit your fault.

628
00:26:34,093 --> 00:26:36,903
And definitely mine.

629
00:26:36,929 --> 00:26:39,299
[ Chuckles ]
You weren't even there.

630
00:26:40,900 --> 00:26:42,700
That's right.

631
00:26:42,735 --> 00:26:44,665
I wasn't there.

632
00:26:44,704 --> 00:26:49,244
Can we sit down, please,
just for a second?

633
00:26:49,275 --> 00:26:56,815
**

634
00:26:56,849 --> 00:26:58,219
Shaun...

635
00:26:58,250 --> 00:27:00,690
I convinced myself
that everything was fine

636
00:27:00,720 --> 00:27:02,960
because in here,
it is.

637
00:27:02,989 --> 00:27:05,289
It's great.

638
00:27:05,324 --> 00:27:07,294
But you need help.

639
00:27:07,326 --> 00:27:09,696
Shaun...

640
00:27:09,729 --> 00:27:13,299
you need guidance --

641
00:27:13,332 --> 00:27:16,772
much more
than I can give you.

642
00:27:16,803 --> 00:27:19,173
**

643
00:27:19,205 --> 00:27:22,705
I'm supposed to be
with my patient.

644
00:27:22,742 --> 00:27:26,382
I'm supposed to be watching her
like a hawk.

645
00:27:26,412 --> 00:27:31,652
**

646
00:27:45,064 --> 00:27:46,804
[ Monitors beeping ]

647
00:27:46,833 --> 00:27:48,703
It's my fault.

648
00:27:52,905 --> 00:27:54,135
I didn't like her.

649
00:27:54,173 --> 00:27:57,343
When I first saw her
this morning, she just...

650
00:27:57,376 --> 00:28:00,346
didn't look...

651
00:28:00,379 --> 00:28:02,349
I don't know.

652
00:28:08,454 --> 00:28:10,364
I mean,
I wanted to blow her off,

653
00:28:10,389 --> 00:28:12,959
so, uh...
I said I forgot water.

654
00:28:12,992 --> 00:28:15,362
I mean, I figured
we'd go to the store

655
00:28:15,394 --> 00:28:17,364
and -- and I'd pretend
that I forgot my wallet.

656
00:28:17,396 --> 00:28:19,196
I knew she didn't have
her purse, so...

657
00:28:19,231 --> 00:28:23,171
We can't go hiking
without water, right?

658
00:28:23,202 --> 00:28:25,912
I mean,
no harm, no foul?

659
00:28:25,938 --> 00:28:27,938
Mm.

660
00:28:28,975 --> 00:28:33,175
She was there
because of me.

661
00:28:33,212 --> 00:28:35,282
She's here...

662
00:28:35,314 --> 00:28:37,454
because of me.

663
00:28:37,483 --> 00:28:42,193
It's not
a causal relationship.

664
00:28:42,221 --> 00:28:45,121
Wait,
excuse me?

665
00:28:45,157 --> 00:28:48,257
**

666
00:28:48,294 --> 00:28:50,404
It's not
a causal relationship --

667
00:28:50,429 --> 00:28:51,399
lying and shootings.

668
00:28:51,430 --> 00:28:52,500
Lying doesn't
cause shootings,

669
00:28:52,531 --> 00:28:54,001
otherwise,
every time someone lied --

670
00:28:54,033 --> 00:28:55,533
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

671
00:28:55,567 --> 00:28:57,537
Her pulse pressure
is narrow.

672
00:28:57,569 --> 00:28:59,069
Wait,
what does that mean?

673
00:28:59,105 --> 00:29:00,105
She's dying.

674
00:29:00,139 --> 00:29:01,969
Page Melendez.
Stat!

675
00:29:02,008 --> 00:29:05,848
**

676
00:29:05,878 --> 00:29:08,948
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

677
00:29:08,981 --> 00:29:11,281
Your respiratory rate
is up.

678
00:29:11,317 --> 00:29:13,247
Are you
having trouble breathing?

679
00:29:13,285 --> 00:29:14,415
Yeah.
It's tight.

680
00:29:14,453 --> 00:29:19,293
**

681
00:29:22,394 --> 00:29:25,304
Find Dr. Lim.

682
00:29:25,331 --> 00:29:28,571
Narrow pulse pressure indicates
a reduced cardiac output.

683
00:29:28,600 --> 00:29:30,870
The inflammation
is affecting her heart.

684
00:29:30,903 --> 00:29:32,543
She's in
end-stage organ failure.

685
00:29:32,571 --> 00:29:34,511
Yes, we can insert
an intra-aortic balloon pump.

686
00:29:34,540 --> 00:29:36,040
It may reduce some
of the workload on her heart,

687
00:29:36,075 --> 00:29:38,205
but it's failing fast --
really fast.

688
00:29:38,244 --> 00:29:39,914
It only needs
to work overnight.

689
00:29:39,946 --> 00:29:41,846
The inflammatory reaction
will improve after that.

690
00:29:41,881 --> 00:29:43,981
What if it's failing so fast
because it's not her heart?

691
00:29:44,016 --> 00:29:45,376
**

692
00:29:45,417 --> 00:29:47,187
Her hemoglobin's dropped
from 14 to 12

693
00:29:47,219 --> 00:29:48,249
between
her last two draws.

694
00:29:48,287 --> 00:29:50,387
What if the real problem
is she's bleeding somewhere?

695
00:29:50,422 --> 00:29:53,162
Given what she's been
through, a two-point drop
could mean nothing.

696
00:29:53,192 --> 00:29:54,262
Or it could mean
a bleed,

697
00:29:54,293 --> 00:29:55,593
which would account
for the narrow pulse pressure.

698
00:29:55,627 --> 00:29:56,897
Her heart
could be fine.

699
00:29:56,929 --> 00:29:58,499
**

700
00:29:58,530 --> 00:30:00,870
If you're right, that means
we'd have to open her back up.

701
00:30:00,900 --> 00:30:02,900
I don't know if her body
can handle another operation.

702
00:30:02,935 --> 00:30:03,865
No,
it can't.

703
00:30:03,903 --> 00:30:05,973
Treating heart failure
with an aortic pump

704
00:30:06,005 --> 00:30:07,365
is also
a simple procedure.

705
00:30:07,406 --> 00:30:09,206
So we're
going to diagnose

706
00:30:09,241 --> 00:30:11,011
based on which procedure
is simpler?

707
00:30:11,043 --> 00:30:12,913
If I'm right, there could be
no more blood to pump.

708
00:30:12,945 --> 00:30:13,905
She'll be dead.

709
00:30:13,946 --> 00:30:16,346
**

710
00:30:16,382 --> 00:30:18,482
[ Alarm blares ]
She's crashing!

711
00:30:18,517 --> 00:30:20,447
We should prepare the cath lab
for a pump.

712
00:30:20,486 --> 00:30:21,986
We should prepare
the O.R.

713
00:30:22,021 --> 00:30:24,391
**

714
00:30:24,423 --> 00:30:27,563
Let's get her
into an O.R. now.

715
00:30:27,593 --> 00:30:32,103
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

716
00:30:37,403 --> 00:30:39,043
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

717
00:30:39,071 --> 00:30:41,041
Hemoglobin's dropped
to 8.

718
00:30:41,073 --> 00:30:43,083
She is bleeding out.

719
00:30:43,109 --> 00:30:44,379
Yes, she is,
but where?

720
00:30:44,410 --> 00:30:46,110
Got to find
where the bleeder's coming from

721
00:30:46,145 --> 00:30:47,905
and clip it
before she dies.

722
00:30:47,947 --> 00:30:49,317
**

723
00:30:49,348 --> 00:30:50,478
I got nothing.

724
00:30:50,516 --> 00:30:52,376
Must be hidden under the
retroperitoneum or mediastinum.

725
00:30:52,418 --> 00:30:53,918
That's a whole lot
of real estate

726
00:30:53,953 --> 00:30:55,393
to cut open
and just go blindly looking.

727
00:30:55,421 --> 00:30:57,161
We should start at the abdomen.
She was shot there.

728
00:30:57,189 --> 00:30:59,259
The bullet passed through
the posterior thorax.

729
00:30:59,291 --> 00:31:01,131
BP's 40 over palp.
She's dying, Neil.

730
00:31:01,160 --> 00:31:02,960
Whatever you're gonna do,
you need to do it now.

731
00:31:02,995 --> 00:31:05,125
We need to look everywhere.
Give me a knife and sternal saw.

732
00:31:05,164 --> 00:31:06,504
I'm gonna open her up
from chest to pelvis.

733
00:31:06,532 --> 00:31:08,072
**

734
00:31:08,100 --> 00:31:10,500
Prep the sternum and abdomen
with Betadine.

735
00:31:10,536 --> 00:31:12,266
Gonna need
a sponge stick

736
00:31:12,304 --> 00:31:14,274
to control the bleeding
when we find it.

737
00:31:14,306 --> 00:31:17,336
**

738
00:31:23,582 --> 00:31:24,922
Stop!

739
00:31:24,951 --> 00:31:26,621
**

740
00:31:26,652 --> 00:31:32,362
Open her between the second
and third rib on the left side.

741
00:31:32,391 --> 00:31:34,491
The bullet nicked the left
supreme intercostal artery.

742
00:31:34,526 --> 00:31:35,486
The wall has blown.

743
00:31:35,527 --> 00:31:36,627
How do you know?

744
00:31:36,662 --> 00:31:39,502
I followed
the injuries --

745
00:31:39,531 --> 00:31:41,301
pelvis to bowel to spleen
to diaphragm.

746
00:31:41,333 --> 00:31:44,603
Next target has to be
left supreme intercostal artery.

747
00:31:44,636 --> 00:31:45,466
**

748
00:31:45,504 --> 00:31:48,214
All right,
prep left intercostal space.

749
00:31:48,240 --> 00:31:52,110
**

750
00:31:52,144 --> 00:31:53,654
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]
[ Gasping ]

751
00:31:53,679 --> 00:31:55,109
**

752
00:31:55,147 --> 00:31:56,117
I can't breathe.

753
00:31:56,148 --> 00:31:57,678
Why aren't you
helping me?

754
00:31:57,716 --> 00:31:59,646
Dr. Lim will be along
in just two minutes.

755
00:31:59,685 --> 00:32:01,245
You're the damn doctor.
Do your job.

756
00:32:01,287 --> 00:32:03,117
**

757
00:32:03,155 --> 00:32:07,455
[ Gasping ]

758
00:32:07,493 --> 00:32:11,433
[ Beeping continues ]

759
00:32:11,463 --> 00:32:14,473
I need to open up
the left neck compartment

760
00:32:14,500 --> 00:32:16,400
to relieve
the pressure.

761
00:32:16,435 --> 00:32:18,435
Procedure tray?

762
00:32:18,470 --> 00:32:21,710
**

763
00:32:22,774 --> 00:32:24,484
You done this before?

764
00:32:24,510 --> 00:32:26,650
Nope.

765
00:32:26,678 --> 00:32:28,608
Scalpel.

766
00:32:28,647 --> 00:32:35,117
**

767
00:32:35,154 --> 00:32:36,624
It's too swollen.

768
00:32:36,655 --> 00:32:39,085
I can't see
the Adam's apple.

769
00:32:39,125 --> 00:32:40,085
Okay.

770
00:32:40,126 --> 00:32:42,356
Cut along
the soft divot

771
00:32:42,394 --> 00:32:44,764
between the carotid sheath
and the trachea.

772
00:32:44,796 --> 00:32:46,266
Soft divot.

773
00:32:46,298 --> 00:32:50,098
Got it.

774
00:32:50,136 --> 00:32:54,306
**

775
00:33:00,479 --> 00:33:02,509
[ Wheezing ]
Update me.

776
00:33:02,548 --> 00:33:03,548
**

777
00:33:03,582 --> 00:33:06,322
[ Wheezes ]
What did you do?

778
00:33:06,352 --> 00:33:08,322
He had a cervical hematoma.
I had to relieve the pressure.

779
00:33:08,354 --> 00:33:09,324
Here?

780
00:33:09,355 --> 00:33:11,685
**

781
00:33:11,723 --> 00:33:13,533
[ Beeping slows ]

782
00:33:13,559 --> 00:33:15,689
Oxygen sats are going up.

783
00:33:15,727 --> 00:33:17,597
It's rare,

784
00:33:17,629 --> 00:33:19,529
but post-op swelling can happen
with tracheal tears.

785
00:33:19,565 --> 00:33:22,125
That's why we watch them
so closely the first 24 hours.

786
00:33:22,168 --> 00:33:26,338
You mind if we finish this off
in the operating room?

787
00:33:26,372 --> 00:33:28,742
**

788
00:33:28,774 --> 00:33:30,644
I don't see anything,
Shaun --

789
00:33:30,676 --> 00:33:32,536
no blood
and no arterial tear.

790
00:33:32,578 --> 00:33:33,578
You're too high.

791
00:33:33,612 --> 00:33:35,352
It's near
the bifurcation.

792
00:33:35,381 --> 00:33:36,481
Get some light in.

793
00:33:36,515 --> 00:33:40,085
**

794
00:33:41,220 --> 00:33:44,490
I got something. Blood's pooling
right under the bifurcation.

795
00:33:44,523 --> 00:33:45,623
Clamp now.

796
00:33:45,657 --> 00:33:49,427
**

797
00:33:49,461 --> 00:33:51,501
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

798
00:33:51,530 --> 00:33:55,500
**

799
00:33:57,103 --> 00:33:58,373
[ Beeping slows ]
[ Sighs ]

800
00:33:59,671 --> 00:34:01,441
[ Sighs ]

801
00:34:01,473 --> 00:34:03,513
She wasn't
in heart failure.

802
00:34:03,542 --> 00:34:06,152
That means her heart is
still strong enough to get
her through the night.

803
00:34:06,178 --> 00:34:08,708
I was wrong.

804
00:34:08,747 --> 00:34:10,717
Yeah.

805
00:34:10,749 --> 00:34:13,649
And you just
made up for it.

806
00:34:13,685 --> 00:34:15,245
**

807
00:34:15,287 --> 00:34:17,387
You were right,
Jared.

808
00:34:17,423 --> 00:34:20,163
**

809
00:34:20,192 --> 00:34:22,662
Good work.

810
00:34:22,694 --> 00:34:26,404
**

811
00:34:48,354 --> 00:34:50,194
You know what?

812
00:34:50,222 --> 00:34:51,422
You were right.

813
00:34:51,457 --> 00:34:53,227
My mother had problems.

814
00:34:53,259 --> 00:34:55,489
So I couldn't afford
to just around

815
00:34:55,527 --> 00:34:57,497
expecting everything
to be handed to me

816
00:34:57,529 --> 00:35:00,369
or whatever else it is
that's holding you back.

817
00:35:00,399 --> 00:35:02,299
And yeah,
I got some breaks,

818
00:35:02,334 --> 00:35:03,874
but I worked
my ass off.

819
00:35:03,902 --> 00:35:07,312
Two jobs, two roommates
every step of the way.

820
00:35:07,339 --> 00:35:09,779
And that
is what got me to the place

821
00:35:09,808 --> 00:35:12,508
where I could
save your life.

822
00:35:12,544 --> 00:35:16,324
**

823
00:35:18,750 --> 00:35:22,390
[ Sighs ]

824
00:35:27,226 --> 00:35:28,556
Melendez: Your daughter's
not out of the woods yet,

825
00:35:28,594 --> 00:35:30,834
but I do expect her condition
to improve day by day.

826
00:35:30,862 --> 00:35:32,932
Thank you,
Doctor.

827
00:35:32,964 --> 00:35:34,574
Thank you.
You're welcome.

828
00:35:43,609 --> 00:35:45,939
[ Moans ]

829
00:35:45,977 --> 00:35:48,707
Mm.

830
00:35:48,747 --> 00:35:50,277
Hey.
Hi.

831
00:35:50,316 --> 00:35:51,546
Baby.

832
00:35:51,583 --> 00:35:54,193
Sorry we weren't here
for you.

833
00:35:54,220 --> 00:35:55,450
How are you feeling?

834
00:35:55,487 --> 00:35:56,557
Uh...

835
00:35:56,588 --> 00:35:58,618
probably won't be hiking
anytime soon.

836
00:35:58,657 --> 00:35:59,627
[ Chuckles ]

837
00:35:59,658 --> 00:36:02,688
Mm.

838
00:36:02,728 --> 00:36:05,198
Hey.

839
00:36:05,231 --> 00:36:08,771
You sneaking out
before I can thank you?

840
00:36:08,800 --> 00:36:12,200
Please, you don't need
to thank me.

841
00:36:12,238 --> 00:36:13,438
Oh.

842
00:36:13,472 --> 00:36:15,372
Yeah, I do.

843
00:36:15,407 --> 00:36:17,577
And apologize.

844
00:36:17,609 --> 00:36:21,249
I was wrong about you.

845
00:36:21,280 --> 00:36:23,250
**

846
00:36:23,282 --> 00:36:24,722
[ Chuckles ]

847
00:36:24,750 --> 00:36:27,390
I thought you were trying
to ditch me.

848
00:36:27,419 --> 00:36:30,419
**

849
00:36:30,456 --> 00:36:31,386
I was...

850
00:36:31,423 --> 00:36:35,293
hoping you were trying
to ditch me.

851
00:36:35,327 --> 00:36:37,957
[ Chuckles ]

852
00:36:37,996 --> 00:36:41,396
I'm sorry.

853
00:36:41,433 --> 00:36:43,403
**

854
00:36:43,435 --> 00:36:45,865
When you're
feeling better,

855
00:36:45,904 --> 00:36:48,544
I'd like a second chance
at a first date.

856
00:36:48,574 --> 00:36:49,544
**

857
00:36:49,575 --> 00:36:52,735
[ Chuckles ]

858
00:36:52,778 --> 00:36:57,948
**

859
00:37:07,993 --> 00:37:09,903
Claire:
I'm sorry.

860
00:37:09,928 --> 00:37:13,368
**

861
00:37:13,399 --> 00:37:14,629
You were right.

862
00:37:14,666 --> 00:37:16,966
I publicly
disrespected you,

863
00:37:17,002 --> 00:37:19,312
and so
I thought it only right

864
00:37:19,338 --> 00:37:20,738
to publicly respect you.

865
00:37:20,772 --> 00:37:24,312
**

866
00:37:24,343 --> 00:37:25,913
I am grateful

867
00:37:25,944 --> 00:37:28,654
for the chance
to learn from you.

868
00:37:28,680 --> 00:37:30,050
**

869
00:37:30,081 --> 00:37:32,751
I know
you needed this victory.

870
00:37:32,784 --> 00:37:35,324
Glad you saved
a life today.

871
00:37:35,354 --> 00:37:37,594
Just wish
it wasn't a Nazi.

872
00:37:37,623 --> 00:37:45,463
**

873
00:37:49,668 --> 00:37:52,698
[ Footsteps approach ]

874
00:37:59,878 --> 00:38:02,908
[ Sighs ]

875
00:38:06,385 --> 00:38:08,545
[ Dog barks in distance ]

876
00:38:08,587 --> 00:38:10,557
Lane number two.

877
00:38:10,589 --> 00:38:13,019
Maddie always
took that lane.

878
00:38:13,058 --> 00:38:15,088
She would
tuck in behind me

879
00:38:15,126 --> 00:38:18,556
and draft
until the last 200 meters.

880
00:38:18,597 --> 00:38:21,367
It was
a dirty little trick.

881
00:38:21,400 --> 00:38:22,570
[ Chuckles ]

882
00:38:22,601 --> 00:38:24,771
It worked.
Every time.

883
00:38:30,776 --> 00:38:33,006
13 years ago today.

884
00:38:33,044 --> 00:38:35,514
Yeah.

885
00:38:35,547 --> 00:38:38,047
I miss her, too.

886
00:38:41,687 --> 00:38:44,587
Give her space,
right?

887
00:38:44,623 --> 00:38:45,993
Give her space.

888
00:38:46,024 --> 00:38:49,134
She just drifted
farther and farther away.

889
00:38:49,160 --> 00:38:51,530
Everything I did...

890
00:38:51,563 --> 00:38:53,003
I did wrong.

891
00:38:53,031 --> 00:38:55,071
You did your best.

892
00:38:57,569 --> 00:38:58,869
I was...

893
00:38:58,904 --> 00:39:04,014
practically living at your house
back then, and --

894
00:39:04,042 --> 00:39:05,882
If I hadn't...

895
00:39:05,911 --> 00:39:10,621
You were both
[Sighs] teenagers.

896
00:39:10,649 --> 00:39:12,019
You were idiots.

897
00:39:12,050 --> 00:39:14,590
You got lucky,
she didn't.

898
00:39:18,857 --> 00:39:20,527
If I...

899
00:39:20,559 --> 00:39:23,529
was there more...

900
00:39:23,562 --> 00:39:25,032
if I...

901
00:39:25,063 --> 00:39:27,933
stayed on her...

902
00:39:27,966 --> 00:39:30,436
[ Chuckles ]

903
00:39:31,470 --> 00:39:33,570
You're there for him.

904
00:39:38,677 --> 00:39:41,047
[ Chuckles ]

905
00:39:41,079 --> 00:39:42,949
Reporter: Here's your extended
forecast for the week.

906
00:39:42,981 --> 00:39:44,651
Starting off with a little bit
of cloud cover

907
00:39:44,683 --> 00:39:46,053
in San Francisco,
temperatures in the low 70s...

908
00:39:46,084 --> 00:39:47,294
[ Knock on door ]

909
00:39:47,318 --> 00:39:49,918
...just a few degrees as we get
closer to the weekend.

910
00:39:49,955 --> 00:39:52,615
Expect dry conditions
for the next seven days here --

911
00:39:53,625 --> 00:39:56,725
I, uh,
saw your light.

912
00:40:00,031 --> 00:40:02,801
[ Dog barking,
siren wails in distance ]

913
00:40:02,834 --> 00:40:05,174
I'm sorry.

914
00:40:06,171 --> 00:40:08,071
Claire told me
to apologize

915
00:40:08,106 --> 00:40:10,206
because you didn't want me
to tell the truth.

916
00:40:10,241 --> 00:40:12,681
You only wanted me
to support your position,

917
00:40:12,711 --> 00:40:15,051
even though
it's wrong.

918
00:40:16,682 --> 00:40:19,492
Well,
I don't accept.

919
00:40:20,919 --> 00:40:24,819
I may have overreacted
this morning a little.

920
00:40:24,856 --> 00:40:28,556
And you were honest --
brutally honest --

921
00:40:28,594 --> 00:40:33,574
but you shouldn't have to wear
ear plugs in your own home.

922
00:40:33,599 --> 00:40:36,969
And don't start lying to me
to make me feel good.

923
00:40:37,002 --> 00:40:40,112
You're the only honest guy
I know.

924
00:40:40,138 --> 00:40:41,638
[ Scoffs ]

925
00:40:42,674 --> 00:40:45,184
So...

926
00:40:45,210 --> 00:40:47,780
**

927
00:40:47,813 --> 00:40:50,923
...have a good night,
Shaun Murphy.

928
00:40:50,949 --> 00:40:53,789
And I will try
not to keep you up.

929
00:40:53,819 --> 00:40:54,789
[ Chuckles ]

930
00:40:54,820 --> 00:40:59,690
[ Clem Snide's
"I'll Be Your Mirror" plays ]

931
00:40:59,725 --> 00:41:00,585
[ Door closes in distance ]

932
00:41:00,626 --> 00:41:03,856
**

933
00:41:03,895 --> 00:41:06,995
* I'll be your mirror

934
00:41:07,032 --> 00:41:10,002
* Reflect what you are

935
00:41:10,035 --> 00:41:12,735
* In case you don't know

936
00:41:12,771 --> 00:41:15,871
* I'll be the wind

937
00:41:15,907 --> 00:41:19,137
* The rain and the sunset

938
00:41:19,177 --> 00:41:24,677
* The light on your door
to show that you're home *

939
00:41:24,716 --> 00:41:28,016
* 'Cause when you think
the night has seen your mind *

940
00:41:28,053 --> 00:41:31,623
I made
a mistake today.

941
00:41:31,657 --> 00:41:35,927
* That inside
you're twisted and unkind *
And someone got hurt.

942
00:41:35,961 --> 00:41:43,131
* Let me stand to show
that you are blind *

943
00:41:43,168 --> 00:41:49,308
* Please put down your hands

944
00:41:49,340 --> 00:41:53,650
* 'Cause I see you

